-- South African Farmers May Plant 10% Less Land With Corn as Prices Decline
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2010-10-21T13:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/south-african-farmers-may-plant-10-less-land-with-corn-as-prices-decline.html
South Africa may plant 10 percent
less land with corn this season after prices fell.  Farmers may plant corn on 2.47 million hectares, Marda
Scheepers, a spokesman for the Crop Estimates Committee, said by
phone from Pretoria today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Carli Lourens  in Johannesburg at 
